The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to construct a benchmark for the best attainable level of prediction and to test the completeness of theories. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the analysis of data and the assessment of theories, which could fall under the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the application of the framework to domains such as sequential decision-making and repeated zero-sum games, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
